example "can't nobody beat 'em" is a negative inversion construction whereas "Ain't no farmer made money this year." is an existential negative inversion, because it uses the verb "to be."%0a> %0a> %0a> %0a> Source: [[http://ygdp.yale.edu/phenomena/negative-inversion]]%0a> %0a> [[#contentends]]%0a> ----%0a> ----%0a> %0a> !!Expansions:%0a> [[#expansions]]%0a> %0a> [[#expansionsend]]%0a> %0a> ----%0a> %25red%25 '''Add an expansion:'''%0a> %0a> (:if [ exists GradebookExpansions.{$Name}-{$Author} || equal {$Author} {$:Author} ] :)%0a> %0a> (:else:)%0a> %0a> (:foxform Site.FoxForms#newexpansion:)%0a> %0a> (:ifend:)%0a> %0a> ----%0a> ----%0a> %0a> !!Comments%0a> %0a> %0a> %0a> (:section: C:)%0a> (:Category: MorphosyntacticDiversity:)%0a\ No newline at end of file%0a
