t, because "can not" is not allowed; instead, the contraction "can't" must be used.%0a%3c In African American English, there are two kinds of negative inversion, as there is a distinction between negative inversion constructions and existential negative inversion, with the latter being negative inversion where the auxiliary is the copula "be," that is the existential "be." For instance, the previous example "can't nobody beat 'em" is a negative inversion construction whereas "Ain't no farmer made money this year." is an existential negative inversion, because it uses the verb "to be."%0a
